## 12. What to explicitly delete from the current design

Claude should delete or rewrite anything that enforces the wrong backbone.

### Delete

* campaign-first logic as the main APS architecture
* giant same-grade campaign generation across the full backlog
* mandatory campaign-to-campaign sequencing
* APIs that are built around obsolete campaign assumptions
* UI flows that assume campaign is the only planning object

The earlier implementation explicitly created rolling campaign logic and campaign endpoints, then later admitted that this was still solving the wrong problem. That part should not be preserved as-is.  

### Rewrite

* planning UI around Order Pool / Planning Board / Heat Builder / Schedule / Release
* APIs around planning horizon, lot proposal, heat derivation, simulation, and release
* scheduler input model to accept Planning Orders + Heats, not giant campaigns

