## 13. What to keep from the earlier discussion

Not everything from the earlier discussion was wrong. Keep the following insights:

### Keep

* rolling horizon planning
* finite scheduling
* resource conflict handling
* sequence-aware planning
* due-date-driven selection
* planner review before release
* distinction between commercial demand and physical production constraints

### Do not keep

* unsupported exact performance claims
* unsupported “industry standard” claims stated as fact
* one-object-fits-all thinking
* campaign sequencing as the organizing principle

The later discussion itself already acknowledges that earlier numbers and some claims were overconfident and that the architecture had become muddled. Claude should accept that and proceed with a clean rebuild.  

