## 14. The clean statement of intent Claude should follow

Use this as the final guiding statement:

> APS for this steel use case should begin from Sales Orders, automatically propose manufacturable Planning Orders within a short rolling horizon, derive required heat-level batches from those lots, and then finite-schedule the resulting operations on real plant resources using due-date, changeover, and capacity logic.
>
> Campaigns, if retained at all, should only be short-horizon sequence or review groupings in the UI, not the fundamental planning backbone.

